news.title: Manglam Group to redevelop a residential project in Borivali, Mumbai
news.para: Manglam Group launched its first Mumbai redevelopment project, Manglam Rajanigandha, in Borivali (West), with an investment of ₹100 crore. This residential development, spread across 80,000 sq ft, will feature 80 apartments, with half reserved for existing tenants, and is projected to generate ₹150 crore by its June 2026 completion.

news.title: JSW One Platforms raises ₹575 crore
news.para: JSW One Platforms raised ₹575 crore in a May 2025 funding round, attracting investors like SBI and JSW Steel. This capital will be invested in its technology platform, operational expansion, and strengthening its NBFC arm to enhance credit access for small businesses. The company reported a ₹12,567 crore GMV in FY25 and projects over ₹8,000 crore in H1 FY26.

news.title: Sundaram Alternates exits second realty fund with 17% IRR
news.para: Sundaram Alternates successfully closed its second real estate credit fund, SA RE Credit Fund II, delivering a gross investor IRR of 17%. The fund invested entirely in secured, high-yielding debentures from Indian developers. Sundaram Alternates has deployed over ₹4,200 crore across 74 deals, achieving 38 complete exits and generating significant returns for investors.

news.title: Chimbel residents hold prayer to oppose Unity Mall
news.para: Chimbel residents performed a prayer at Kadamba Plateau, opposing the proposed Unity Mall and a 17-storey Prashaasan Stambh, a day after their foundation stone was laid. They fear the projects will destroy Toyaar lake's biodiversity, which serves as a crucial lifeline and historical water source for the community. Residents assert that their beloved nature is in danger.

news.title: ₹600 crore fund, but no infrastructure for construction workers in Goa: Government data
news.para: Goa's Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board collected Rs 600 crore but spent nothing on mandated physical infrastructure or basic facilities. A CAG audit revealed systemic failures, including poor scheme implementation, low beneficiary registration, and the board's inability to execute its own decisions, compounded by infrequent meetings and staff shortages.

news.title: Groundwater salinity a threat to buildings in 17 areas of Mumbai
news.para: Report says groundwater quality good in only two areas - one at Ismail Yusuf College, Jogeshwari, other at Film City in Goregaon

news.title: Goa CM urges central government to allow manual sand mining in state
news.para: Goa's Chief Minister urged the Union government to relax sand extraction guidelines, advocating for traditional methods in rivers due to CRZ prohibitions and livelihood impacts. The state seeks amendments to CRZ Notifications and introduced a star rating system for minor minerals to promote sustainable, ESG-compliant mining practices, ensuring transparency and accountability in operations.

news.title: Telangana housing board to auction plots & flats across GHMC from October 6
news.para: Telangana Housing Board will auction plots and flats across GHMC limits and other districts starting Monday. These sales, conducted through open and e-auctions in areas like Chintal, Nizampet, and KPHB Colony, aim to fund the Indiramma Housing Scheme. The board anticipates transferring 1,618 crore for the scheme, building on recent successful auctions.

news.title: Odisha REAT backs buyer over delayed possession from builder, lack of amenities
news.para: The Odisha Real Estate Appellate Tribunal (OREAT) dismissed a city-based realtor's appeal, upholding an earlier order to compensate a homebuyer for delayed possession and unfulfilled promises. The developer's claim that RERA was inapplicable was rejected, as their completion certificates were deemed invalid. OREAT directed the builder to pay interest, obtain valid occupancy certificates, and provide all promised amenities.

news.title: SGRA chairman urges Pune housing societies to follow Mumbai model of self-redevelopment
news.para: Pravin Darekar, SGRA chairman, advocates for self-redevelopment, highlighting its benefits for property owners. He noted its rapid popularity in Mumbai and urged Pune societies to adopt it, citing lower interest loans from government banks. A dedicated authority and Mhada will expedite projects, ensuring all profits benefit society members directly.

news.title: Seven years on, flats not handed over, buyers of Aashiyara 37C protest against builder in Gurugram
news.para: Hundreds of Aashiyara 37C homebuyers protested in Gurugram, demanding possession of their homes after paying full cost years ago. The developer, Renuka Traders, allegedly missed 12 deadlines, diverted funds, and abandoned the site, leaving buyers in severe financial and emotional distress. They seek urgent regulatory action and a binding completion plan.

news.title: US home builders, homeowners brace for impact of kitchen tariffs
news.para: President Trump's new 50% tariffs on imported kitchen cabinets and bathroom vanities, along with 30% on upholstered furniture, are set to begin Oct. 14. Industry experts deem them "comically nonsensical," anticipating increased costs across the entire market, from budget to high-end, and a potential "cascading effect" on home renovation projects and various trades.

news.title: Britain's government looks to streamline home-buying process
news.para: Britain's government announced plans to streamline the home-buying process, aiming to cut four weeks off the typical five-month timeline. Proposals include requiring pre-listing surveys and binding contracts to halve failed transactions and save first-time buyers an average of £710. This initiative supports the government's goal of boosting the property market.

news.title: Warburg Pincus to infuse ₹500 crore more in Truhome Finance
news.para: Affordable housing lender Truhome Finance is set to receive another Rs 500 crore from Warburg Pincus, bringing total investment to over Rs 2,000 crore. The company targets aggressive growth, aiming for Rs 23,000 crore AUM this fiscal and expanding its branch network and workforce, primarily serving the self-employed segment. An IPO is also on the cards.

news.title: Telangana HC pulls up Badangpet civic body over illegal constructions
news.para: The Telangana High Court has directed the Badangpet Municipal Corporation to take immediate action against illegal constructions on encroached public land. This order followed a residents' association complaint about a firm encroaching a 40-ft road. Despite prior demolition, violators resumed construction, prompting the court to demand strict enforcement and compliance with layout provisions.

news.title: Gurugram metro phase-I faces delay: Month after official launch, project held up by encroachments
news.para: Gurgaon's new metro line project, despite a recent groundbreaking ceremony, faces significant delays on the ground. Contractors are unable to mobilize machinery or begin segment production because a crucial 5.2-hectare casting yard site in Sector 33 remains heavily encroached. Officials are actively working with authorities to clear the land, with some preliminary pre-construction activities already underway.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh housing board holds e-auction of 992 properties
news.para: The UP Housing and Development Board successfully e-auctioned 992 properties, including residential and non-residential plots, on September 30 across multiple cities. This mega auction is projected to generate Rs 1,168.43 crore. The proceeds will fund new housing projects, infrastructure improvements, and affordable housing, setting a new benchmark for UP's real estate sector.

news.title: MHADA revises premium charges for commercial area in redevelopment projects
news.para: MHADA updated its 2007 redevelopment rules, easing premiums on additional commercial space in layouts, addressing developers’ concerns about financial viability of projects.

news.title: HYDRAA reclaims land worth ₹3,600 crore in Kondapur
news.para: HYDRAA reclaimed 36 acres of government land worth Rs 3,600 crore in Kondapur, marking its second-most valuable recovery to date. This prime land, illegally occupied for years, was cleared following a high court directive. The agency previously recovered 317 acres valued at Rs 15,000 crore in Gajularamaram, highlighting its ongoing efforts against encroachment in high-demand urban areas.
